pullRequest.bodyText:
This commit improves the C API for processing output table updates
produced by DDlog.  A successful transaction generates a set of inserts
and deletes to multiple output tables.  We refer to this set of changes
as "delta".  In the Rust API it is represented by the DeltaMap data
type.
A delta is generated by the ddlog_transaction_commit_dump_changes()
method.  In the Rust API it returns an instance of DeltaMap, allowing
the caller to manipulate the delta in a number of ways:

Return it directly to the user.
Merge it with previous deltas to maintain a snapshot of output tables.
Merge deltas over several transactions and clean them up once the
whole bunch has been processed.
Some combination of the above.

The C API did not have the same flexibility, as instead of returning the
delta object it simply invoked a callback for each record in the output.
This commit exports deltas to C as a new type of opaque handle with the
following API:
/* Creates an empty delta.  */
extern ddlog_delta* ddlog_new_delta(void);

/* Retrieve changes to a specific table.  */
extern ddlog_delta* ddlog_delta_get_table(const ddlog_delta *delta, table_id table);

/* Enumerate changes in this delta. */
extern void ddlog_delta_enumerate(
    const ddlog_delta *delta,
    void (*cb)(uintptr_t arg,
               table_id table,
               const ddlog_record *rec,
               bool polarity),
    uintptr_t cb_arg);

/* Remove changes to the specified table from `delta` and return them as a separate
 * delta. */
extern void ddlog_delta_clear_table(ddlog_delta *delta, table_id table);

/* Remove changes to the specified table from `delta`. */
extern ddlog_delta* ddlog_delta_remove_table(ddlog_delta *delta, table_id table);

/* Clear changes to all tables.  Leaves `delta` empty. */
extern void ddlog_delta_clear(ddlog_delta *delta);

/* Adds the contents of `new_delta` to `delta`. */
extern void ddlog_delta_union(ddlog_delta *delta, const ddlog_delta *new_delta);

/* Deallocate delta.  Invalidates the pointer. */
extern void ddlog_free_delta(ddlog_delta *delta);

commit.message:
ddlog.h: Delta API.

This commit improves the C API for processing output table updates
produced by DDlog.  A successful transaction generates a set of inserts
and deletes to multiple output tables.  We refer to this set of changes
as "delta".  In the Rust API it is represented by the `DeltaMap` data
type.

A delta is generated by the `ddlog_transaction_commit_dump_changes()`
method.  In the Rust API it returns an instance of `DeltaMap`, allowing
the caller to manipulate the delta in a number of ways:

- Return it directly to the user.
- Merge it with previous deltas to maintain a snapshot of output tables.
- Merge deltas over several transactions and clean them up once the
  whole bunch has been processed.
- Some combination of the above.

The C API did not have the same flexibility, as instead of returning the
delta object it simply invoked a callback for each record in the output.

This commit exports deltas to C as a new type of opaque handle with the
following API:

```
/* Creates an empty delta.  */
extern ddlog_delta* ddlog_new_delta(void);

/* Retrieve changes to a specific table.  */
extern ddlog_delta* ddlog_delta_get_table(const ddlog_delta *delta, table_id table);

/* Enumerate changes in this delta. */
extern void ddlog_delta_enumerate(
    const ddlog_delta *delta,
    void (*cb)(uintptr_t arg,
               table_id table,
               const ddlog_record *rec,
               bool polarity),
    uintptr_t cb_arg);

/* Remove changes to the specified table from `delta` and return them as a separate
 * delta. */
extern void ddlog_delta_clear_table(ddlog_delta *delta, table_id table);

/* Remove changes to the specified table from `delta`. */
extern ddlog_delta* ddlog_delta_remove_table(ddlog_delta *delta, table_id table);

/* Clear changes to all tables.  Leaves `delta` empty. */
extern void ddlog_delta_clear(ddlog_delta *delta);

/* Adds the contents of `new_delta` to `delta`. */
extern void ddlog_delta_union(ddlog_delta *delta, const ddlog_delta *new_delta);

/* Deallocate delta.  Invalidates the pointer. */
extern void ddlog_free_delta(ddlog_delta *delta);

```
